WEBVTT

00:00.706 --> 00:10.779
Hi there, today we'll look at self-training with noisy student improves ImageNet classification by T. Z. Sie, Min Tan Luong, Edward Hovey and Kwok Wili.

00:11.721 --> 00:24.638
So this paper takes an ImageNet classifier that's been trained on the ImageNet dataset and uses that classifier as a teacher model to label a whole bunch of unlabeled images.

00:24.618 --> 00:31.186
And then it trains a student model that is larger than the original teacher model on those teacher labeled images.

00:31.666 --> 00:37.253
And that turns out to improve the classification on the ImageNet validation set.

00:37.734 --> 00:43.020
Now that there is a couple of things that make this all work.

00:43.861 --> 00:50.389
And today we're going to explore how this paper does it and what they say is important.

00:50.369 --> 00:57.526
If you enjoy content like this, as always, don't hesitate to share it out or tell your friends about it.

00:58.187 --> 01:00.292
And if you're not subscribed yet, then do so.

01:01.435 --> 01:05.003
I would appreciate that and you'll get more content.

